<h2>Agents That Remember</h2>

<p>Traditional chatbots are stateless — each conversation starts fresh. Agentic AI systems maintain memory across sessions: they remember previous conversations, learn from user feedback, accumulate knowledge about your business, and build richer context over time.</p>

<p>This persistent memory is what makes agents genuinely useful for complex ongoing work. It's also a new attack target. If an attacker can influence what an agent stores in memory, they can shape its future behavior — persistently, across all sessions, until the poisoning is found and removed.</p>

